  <title>Matlab: Embracing Complexity</title>
  <text xml:space="preserve"><note-content version="0.1">Matlab: Embracing Complexity

<datetime>Tuesday, June 18, 2013 10:58 AM</datetime>

<bold>Platform for Collaboration</bold>

<list><list-item dir="ltr">Car Adaptive cruise control: 
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Neural Imaging of Brain activity
<list><list-item dir="ltr">Uses SPM (statistical parameter mapping)
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">SPM includes
<list><list-item dir="ltr">General linear modeling
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Time series analysis
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Brain connectivity - between different regions
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Structural Changes - pathology and archeological changes of brain.</list-item></list></list-item></list></list-item></list>

<bold>Modeling &amp; Simulation:</bold>

<list><list-item dir="ltr">Microgrid system - (ex. Wind Power plant control system)</list-item></list>

<bold>Automation Modeling

Cyber-Physical Systems

</bold><list><list-item dir="ltr">a network of interacting elements with physical input &amp; output instead of as  standalone devices.
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Hybrid models - Multiform time, Human In Loop (HIL), Continuous  &amp; discrete
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Control Systems - Adaptive &amp; predictive cotnrol, Network control, intelligent systems
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Concurrency, communication &amp; inter operability
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">validation &amp; verification
</list-item><list-item dir="ltr">Autonomous car control &amp; traffic management.</list-item></list></note-content></text>
